The paper deals with compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The focus is on recovery guarantees for signals with structured sparsity, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses applications to binary sampling, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
